    "type": "message",
    "text": "in my experiments with non-typable characters I tried using control+meta+letter keys but I could never remember them. Instead I suggest a universal keyword syntax with autocompletion, similar to what desktop chat systems use (slack, discord, etc.).  Something like “: lin” and then it pops up with completions for ‘link’. Once selected the keyword is replaced with the actual symbol.",
